1 agreement to incorporate modifications to a family-specific improvement
2 plan or diversion agreement; and
3 (f) Provide case management services to assist the family in achieving the goals
4 of the family-specific improvement plan.
5 (2) (a) Upon the accrual of fifteen (15) unexcused absences by a student who is
6 participating in the SOAR Program, the court-designated worker shall
7 notify the county attorney and shall provide the county attorney with a
8 report on the efforts and results of the SOAR Program's work with the
9 student and the parent, guardian, or other person exercising custodial
10 control or supervision of the student.
11 (b) 1. The county attorney shall, upon review of the report, determine if
12 court intervention is appropriate against the student.
13 2. If the county attorney determines that court intervention is appropriate
14 against the student, he or she shall notify the director of pupil
15 personnel to immediately file a habitual truancy complaint.
16 SECTION 3. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 159 IS CREATED TO
17 READ AS FOLLOWS:
18 In addition to the duties assigned under Section 4 of this Act, the director of pupil
19 personnel, or an assistant appointed under KRS 159.080 shall:
20 (1) Upon a student in grades six (6) through twelve (12) becoming a truant as
21 defined in KRS 159.150(1), provide written notice to the student and the student's
22 parent, guardian, or other person exercising custodial control or supervision of
23 the following:
24 (a) The number of the student's unexcused absences;
25 (b) An explanation of the attendance policy, including policies for required
26 documentation for excused absences;
27 (c) Available resources and tools intended to prevent further unexcused
