17 SECTION 5. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 160 IS CREATED TO
18 READ AS FOLLOWS:
19 (1) As used in this section:
20 (a) "Complaint" has the same meaning as in Section 9 of this Act;
21 (b) "Court-designated worker" has the same meaning as in Section 9 of this
22 Act; and
23 (c) "Habitual truant" has the same meaning as in KRS 159.150(3).
24 (2) The purpose of this section is to require the collection and reporting of data that
25 will aid in the understanding of the impact that various interventions have on the
26 attendance of students who are habitually truant.
27 (3) Beginning in the 2027-2028 school year, each school district shall document the
