5 the original order was issued;
6 2. Make a determination during the adjudicatory hearing that the child
7 violated the valid court order; and
8 3. Within forty-eight (48) hours after the adjudicatory hearing on the
9 violation of a valid court order by the child, exclusive of weekends and
10 holidays, receive and review a written report prepared by an appropriate
11 public agency that reviews the behavior of the child and the
12 circumstances under which the child was brought before the court,
13 determines the reasons for the child's behavior, and determines whether
14 all dispositions other than [secure ]detention have been exhausted or are
15 inappropriate. If a prior written report is included in the child's file, that
16 report shall not be used to satisfy this requirement. The child may be
17 [securely ]detained in accordance with Section 10 of this Act for a
18 period not to exceed forty-eight (48) hours, exclusive of weekends and
19 holidays, pending receipt and review of the report by the court. The
20 hearing shall be conducted in accordance with KRS 610.060. The
21 findings required by this subsection shall be included in any order issued
22 by the court which results in the secure or nonsecure detention of a
23 status offender; and
24 (e) If the child is charged with a public offense[,] or contempt on a public
25 offense, and the county in which the case is before the court is served by a
26 state -operated secure detention facility under the statewide detention plan, the
27 child shall be referred to the Department of Juvenile Justice for a security
