5 Section 21. KRS 630.080 is amended to read as follows:
6 (1) (a) In order for the court to detain a child after the detention hearing, the
7 Commonwealth shall establish probable cause at the detention hearing that the
8 child is a status offender and that further detention of the child is necessary for
9 the protection of the child or the community.
10 (b) If the Commonwealth fails to establish probable cause that the child is a status
11 offender, the complaint shall be dismissed and the child shall be released.
12 (c) If the Commonwealth establishes probable cause that the child is a status
13 offender, but that further detention of the child is not necessary for the
14 protection of the child or the community, the child shall be released to the
15 parent or person exercising custodial control or supervision of the child.
16 (d) If grounds are established that the child is a status offender, and that further
17 detention is necessary, the child may be placed in a nonsecure setting
18 approved by the Department of Juvenile Justice;
